{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = AllahDad Bohyo | native_name = '''ڊاڪٽر الهداد ٻوهيو''' | native_name_lang = sd | image = | imagesize = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = AllahDad Bohyo | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1934|08|8}} | birth_place = [[Larkana Now Kamber Shahdadkot, Pakistan|Kamber]] [[Sindh]], British India | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1994|07|16|1934|08|8}} | death_place = | occupation = Teacher, linguist,Poet, and Philosopher | nationality = Pakistani | citizenship = Pakistani | education = PhD | alma_mater = [[University of Sindh]] | period = 1977 | genre = [[Aesthetic]] | subject = Sindhi Language | movement = [[Progressivism|Progressive]] | notableworks = | spouse = Muhammad Ali, Sindhya , Haya o Nisa and Nasraan | partner = Noor Jahan | children = | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | website = {{url|allahdadbohyo.webs.com}} | portaldisp = }}
'''AllahDad Bohyo''' ({{lang-sd|'''ڊاڪٽر الهداد ٻوهيو'''}}) was born on 18 August 1934 in village Pechoha, [[Larkana District]], [[Sindh]]. He was a known writer, educationist, scholar, [[linguist]] and poet. He died on 16 July 1994.<ref>{{citebook|title=Legends of Modern Sindh|author=Prof Hassan Bux Noonari|publisher=Roshni Publications|date=2015|page=74}}</ref>
==Education== He did Master of Arts in English and Bachelor of Teaching. He got PhD degree in 1977 under the supervision of [[Ghulam Ali Allana]] from [[University of Sindh]]. The topic of his research article was "Sindhi Boli jo Samaji Karaj" {{lang-sd|'''سنڌي ٻوليءَ جو سماجي ڪارج'''}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.encyclopediasindhiana.org/article.php?Dflt=%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF+%D9%BB%D9%88%D9%87%D9%8A%D9%88++%DA%8A%D8%A7%DA%AA%D9%BD%D8%B1|title=الهداد ٻوهيو ڊاڪٽر : (Sindhianaسنڌيانا)|website=www.encyclopediasindhiana.org|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>
==Professional career== Dr. AllahDad Bohyo started his practical life as a teacher in 1957. Later on he was promoted as director of education and remained on this post till the last days of his life. Dr. Bohyo is known as literary circle with his criticism and linguistic qualities.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}} He worked his whole life for the promotion of language and literature,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpcs.org.pk/legendsofsindh/|title=Center For Peace & Civil Society CPCS|website=www.cpcs.org.pk}}</ref> his favorite fields were research and he took a deep interest in social linguistics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sindhsalamat.com/threads/13781/|title=محقق، نقاد ۽ تعليمدان ڊاڪٽر الهداد ٻوهيو|publisher=|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=May 2016|reason=source appears to be a user contributed blog entry}}
==Publications== His PhD thesis was published by [[Institute of Sindhology]] in 1978. His articles and essays have been published in different periodicals and newspapers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sindhiadabiboard.org/catalogue/Tanqeed/Book5/Book_page25.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619042651/http://www.sindhiadabiboard.org/catalogue/Tanqeed/Book5/Book_page25.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2015-06-19|title=Sindhi Adabi Board Online Library (Dramas)|date=2015-06-19|access-date=2018-08-27}}</ref> He has also written some books on research and criticism.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://sl.sindhila.org/en/publications/books/item/196-sindhi-boli-a-babat-maqala-ain-mazmoon-volume-iii |title=Archived copy |access-date=19 May 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604102141/http://sl.sindhila.org/en/publications/books/item/196-sindhi-boli-a-babat-maqala-ain-mazmoon-volume-iii |archive-date=4 June 2016 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> It includes "Tanqeedaan" in 1980. Adab ja fikri moharik ({{lang-sd|'''ادب جا فڪري محرڪ'''}}) in 1984 and Ilm Tahkqee in 1970. Dr. Bohyo has compiled a book on poetry named "Chawanda karo Karo" ({{lang-sd|'''چوندا ڪارو ڪارو'''}}) but so far it has not published.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}}
==Death== He died on 16 July 1994 from a heart attack while he was addressing a Seminar at Tando Adam, Sindh.
