'''Cyprus''' or '''Cypriot Sign Language''' ({{lang-el|Κυπριακή Νοηματική Γλώσσα}}) is an incipient [[sign language]] of Cyprus. It appears to be a pidgin of [[American Sign Language]] and [[Greek Sign Language]], not yet a fully developed language. The Greek Cypriot deaf community predominantly uses the [[Greek Sign Language]] (the Turkish Cypriot deaf community uses the [[Turkish Sign Language]]).<ref>Timmermans, 2005, ''The Status of Sign Languages in Europe''</ref>

