{{selfref|For assistance with IPA transcriptions of Estonian for Wikipedia articles, see [[Help:IPA/Estonian and Finnish]].}}
{{IPA notice}}
This article is about the [[phonology]] and [[phonetics]] of the [[Estonian language]].

==Vowels==
[[File:Estonian vowel chart.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Estonian vowel chart, from {{Harvcoltxt|Asu|Teras|2009|p=368}}. For some speakers, {{IPA|/ɤ/}} can be more back (closer to {{IPA|/o/}}), or more back and higher (closer to {{IPA|/u/}}).]]
There are 9 vowels and 36 diphthongs, 28 of which are native to Estonian.<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Ross|Lehiste|2001|p=40}}</ref> All nine vowels can appear as the first component of a diphthong, but only {{IPA|/ɑ e i o u/}} occur as the second component. A vowel characteristic of Estonian is the unrounded back vowel {{IPA|/ɤ/}}, which may be [[close-mid back unrounded vowel|close-mid back]], [[close back unrounded vowel|close back]], or [[close-mid central unrounded vowel|close-mid central]].<ref name="Asu 2009 369"/>

{| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center"
|+ Estonian vowel phonemes<ref name="Asu 2009 368">{{Harvcoltxt|Asu|Teras|2009|p=368}}</ref>
