* {{IPA|/y, ø, ɤ, æ/}} occur only in initial syllables. Other vowels ({{IPA|/i, u, e, o, ɑ/}}) can occur in both initial and non-initial syllables, but {{IPA|/o/}} occurs in non-initial syllables only in proper names and loanwords.<ref name="Asu 2009 369"/>
* The front vowels {{IPA|/y, ø, æ/}} are phonetically near-front {{IPA|[{{IPA link|y|ÿ}}, {{IPA link|ø|ø̈}}, {{IPA link|æ|æ̈}}]}}.<ref name="Asu 2009 368"/>
* Before and after {{IPA|/j/}}, the back vowels {{IPA|/u, ɑ/}} can be fronted to {{IPA|[u̟, ɑ̽]}}.<ref name="Asu 2009 369"/>
* The unrounded vowel transcribed {{IPA|/ɤ/}} can be realized as close back {{IPAblink|ɯ}}, close-mid central {{IPAblink|ɘ}} or close-mid back {{IPAblink|ɤ}}, depending on the speaker.<ref name="Asu 2009 369"/>
* The mid vowels {{IPA|/e, ø, o/}} are phonetically close-mid {{IPA|[{{IPA link|e}}, {{IPA link|ø}}, {{IPA link|o}}]}}.<ref name="Asu 2009 368"/>
* Word-final {{IPA|/e/}} is often realized as mid {{IPAblink|e̞}}.<ref name="Asu 2009 369"/>
* The open vowels {{IPA|[æ, ɑ]}} are phonetically near-open {{IPA|[{{IPA link|æ|æ̈}}, {{IPA link|ɑ|ɑ̝}}]}}.<ref name="Asu 2009 368"/>

