There are very few instances of vowel [[allophony]]; for instance, the long {{IPA|/y/}} is pronounced as the [[diphthong]] {{IPA|[yi]}} in certain{{which|date=May 2017}} environments.

Simple vowels can be inherently short or long, written with single and double vowel letters respectively. Diphthongs are always inherently long. Furthermore, long vowels and diphthongs have two [[suprasegmental]] lengths. This is described [[#Prosody|further below]].

