{{Infobox language |name=Kepo' |altname= |states=[[Indonesia]] |region=Central [[Flores]] |speakers=6,000 |date=2010 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian languages|Nuclear MP]] |fam4=[[Central–Eastern Malayo-Polynesian languages|Central–Eastern MP]] |fam5=[[Sumba–Flores languages|Sumba–Flores]] |fam6=Ende–Manggarai |fam7=Central Flores |iso3=kuk |glotto=kepo1237 |glottorefname=Kepo' }}
'''Kepo’''' (Kepoq) is a possible [[Malayo-Polynesian language]] spoken on [[Flores]] in [[Indonesia]]. It's not clear that it's a separate language from its neighbors.
==References== {{reflist}}
