'''Noor ul Huda Shah''' is a Pakistani dramatist and former caretaker minister.<ref>https://www.dawn.com/news/799025</ref> She is well-known [[Sindh]]i language and [[Urdu language]] [[playwright]], [[novelist]] and a former Provincial Minister of [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.samaa.tv/pakistan/2018/02/voters-never-jahil-noorul-huda-shah-klf/ |title=Voters are never ignorant: Noorul Huda Shah at Karachi Literary Festival|publisher= Samaa TV News|date= 9 February 2018|accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref> She is known for writing popular TV serials like ''Jungle'', [[Marvi]], ''Bebak'', ''Meri Adhuri Moahabat'', ''Ajayb Ghar'', ''Adhoora Milan'' and ''Ishq Gumshuda''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/you/96832-A-tale-of-two-sessions|title= A tale of two sessions|publisher=The News International (newspaper)|date=8 February 2016|accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geo.tv/latest/61562-dallas-iftar-dinner-hosted-in-honor-of-noor-ul-huda |title=Dallas: Iftar dinner hosted in honor of Noor ul Huda|author=Raja Zahid Akhtar Khanzada|publisher=Geo TV News|date=16 July 2013|accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://iblagh.com/en/gen-zias-era-taught-writers-stand-truth-says-sindhi-writer-noor-ul-huda-shah/ General Zia’s era taught writers to stand up for truth] Iblagh News website, Published 20 July 2017, Retrieved 14 February 2018</ref>
==Education== She completed her graduation from [[Sindh University]] and started her career from [[Pakistan Television Corporation]] (PTV). 1983 was a milestone year for her, when her first play ‘Jungle’ was aired on PTV which was a big success and received several awards.<ref>[http://pakistanmediaupdates.com/noor-ul-huda-shah-joins-bol-network-8881.html Noor ul Huda Shah Joins Bol Network] Pakistan Media Updates website, Published 6 April 2017, Retrieved 14 February 2018</ref><ref name=Dawn>{{cite web|url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1173882 |title=Dramas present women as machines, says Noor ul Huda Shah|publisher=Dawn (newspaper)|author=Sadaf Haider|date=8 October 2015|accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=IMDb>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm8898393/ Noor ul Huda Shah on IMDb website] Retrieved 14 February 2018</ref>
